textContent:
Worried - what will we see, where will we go, what will we do in Bayfield? Will we see all the things and make our time worth it? Or will we miss all the things and regret it? Will it be too cold? Will I feel better? Will we spend too much? Will the kids get along? Will gil feel good? Will we have those "special" moments that we see on TV, the one where the family looks at each other and smiling and says how much they love each other?

Tired - crappy sleep. Tossing and turning. Waking up thinking about work. About marketing the brand. About getting out of the teams way. About getting all the work done. I need to learn how to "start up" and "close out" each day. A routine that allows my mind to come back to the present without being whiplashed into the future or the past.
